Natural stone lifting is pleasant because every stone is a sort of puzzle, you have to figure out how to grip it well so it doesn't slip, how to balance its asymmetry and hoist it in the air. Can't really replace barbell but it's so fun to do occasionally

Accepting the asymmetry of one's own body (e.g. when doing one-arm overhead dumbbell presses, it's natural for the bar path and shoulder rotation to be different for the two shoulders, most people do better rotating the left more inwards) is a key for proper theology of the body.
